{
  "text": "Another option to improve the non-invasive diagnosis of liver fibrosis or cirrhosis is the combined use of tests. Here, besides de APRI score, the options are the FibroTest and the FibroScan. In a recent evaluation of these tests in a sample of 183 CHC patients, the area under the ROC curve for the diagnosis of significant fibrosis was 0.78, 0.85 and 0.83, respectively. For the diagnosis of advanced fibrosis these areas were 0.84, 0.9 and 0.9. Finally, the areas for the diagnosis of cirrhosis were 0.83, 0.87 and 0.95. The highest diagnostic yield was obtained by the combined use of FibroTest and FibroScan. Here, the areas under the ROC curve were 0.88, 0.95 and 0.95 for the diagnosis of significant fibrosis, advanced fibrosis and cirrhosis, respectively. [CITATION_1] The combined use of these two non-invasive tests in our setting is, however, almost impossible due to their limited availability and high cost.",
